benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/bundles - Retrieve a bundle by external key

covered: GET - Valid Request: Happy path returning 200 with application/json and a JSON array of Bundle objects (including single and multiple matches).
GET - Empty Response/Not Found: 404 scenarios when no bundle exists or DB empty.
GET - Query Parameters: externalKey required/empty/missing, includedDeleted=true/false, audit=FULL/MINIMAL/NONE, invalid values for includedDeleted and audit, and extra unsupported params handling.
GET - Authorization: 401 (no token) and 403 (insufficient permissions) covered.
Response schema: Bundle object required fields validated; array semantics covered including duplicate externalKey case.
gaps: GET - Caching Behavior: No checks for ETag/If-None-Match, Last-Modified/If-Modified-Since, or Cache-Control/Expires headers.
GET - Rate Limiting: No scenarios for throttling/burst traffic leading to 429 or proper headers (Retry-After) and behavior.

Default parameter behavior not explicitly validated: omitting audit should default to NONE (no audit fields) and omitting includedDeleted should default to false; current tests only validate explicit values.
Pagination: Likely not applicable for this endpoint; if any server-side pagination exists for arrays, it is not tested.
recommendations: Add caching tests: verify presence/values of Cache-Control and ETag headers on 200 responses; add conditional request with If-None-Match expecting 304 when unchanged.
Add rate limiting tests: simulate burst of requests to validate 429 response or documented behavior and presence of Retry-After headers.

Add scenarios to assert default behaviors when parameters are omitted: (a) omit audit and verify no audit fields are returned; (b) omit includedDeleted and verify deleted bundles are excluded (404 for deleted-only match).
Confirm pagination is not supported; if it is, add tests for page/limit parameters and boundary conditions.
